              Job description:

JOB PURPOSE:

Join the Global Data Platform Team and be part of a very successful growing company.
As a Senior Data Engineer, you will be working with highly competent DBAs, Developers, Analysts, and Architects in a technologically diverse environment across the globe. You will design, develop & support modern Data Solutions for our Global customers. You will use modern technologies like SQL Server, Azure SQL DB, Oracle DB, and the Azure Cloud Data platform technologies such as ADF, LogicApp, Azure Functions, Azure Synapse, and ADLS.



RESPONSIBILITIES:

• Meet with stakeholders and individual contributors, including Business and Technology, to understand and document current-state enterprise data & process architecture;
• Understand application data and its use across the enterprise to define data standards and implement business and technology enabling solutions. Work as a Data Engineer on full-lifecycle projects;
• To provide creative solutions for data-related problems at scale by mixing in house and open-source technologies; 
• To help build robust data pipelines and ETL tools, find and evaluate new data sources for acquisition and integration; 
• Enable effective decision making by retrieving and aggregating data from multiple sources and extracting information from complex data sets;
• Mine and analyze data sets across various touchpoints (files, web, app, marketing platforms) to provide actionable insights for business teams to make data-driven decisions; 
• Responsible for building real-time and batch data ingestion pipelines, integrating different data sources like RDBMS, data warehouses, APIs, plant legacy systems, historian systems, file storage systems, etc;
• Work closely with business stakeholders to ensure data definitions and technical logic specifications align with business requirements;
• Perform data extractions via SQL and recommend data visualization and dashboards to businesses.



SKILLS:

• Azure Data Factory
• Azure Datawarehouse
• Azure Synapse Analytics
• Azure SQL Database 
• Azure Data Lake Storage
• Azure Data Bricks \ Bigdata
• Delta lake \ Lakehouse
• Azure Logic App \ Azure Functions
• Azure Cognitive Services
• Azure AI & ML services.
• Python
• Power BI
Must have Azure Data Engineer \ Azure AI Engineer Certifications.



REQUIREMENTS:

• Minimum 6 years of experience in a similar role;
• Expertise with ADLS v1 (v2 preferred) for DataLake design, importing data and administration using both command line and GUI interface;
• Expertise with Azure Data Factory, Azure Synapse (DWH), and Azure Data Bricks; 
• Understanding of MDM (Master Data Management) principles;
• Expert level exposure with Stored Procedures, Triggers, Functions, and SQL Code tuning; 
• Broad range of development skills across the Microsoft stack, e.g. SQL Server, Integration Services (SSIS), Analysis Services (SSAS), Reporting Services (SSRS) from versions 2005 to 2019;
• Experienced with the Azure stack and Microsoft PaaS offerings like Azure SQL Database and Azure SQL Data Warehouse plus orchestration products like Azure Data Factory, Azure Synapse (DWH), and Azure Data Bricks;
• Design, develop and maintain appropriately scaled, effective ETL solutions to support data loading, processing, reports generation and reconciliation using Microsoft SQL Server (SSIS, SSRS, SSAS, etc.), .NET, and related tools;
• Must have experience with Azure SQL Data Warehouse (now Azure Synapse Analytics) or Microsoft Parallel Data Warehouse;
• Experience in building complex data sets from multiple data sources, both internally and externally;
• Expertise in developing ETL/ELT workflows;
• Experience in data visualization reporting architecture and BI tools (e.g. Tableau, Qlik Sense, Power BI); 
• Experience in Cloud platform - Azure eco-system;
• Experience working with different data storage options, including Azure BLOB storage, ADLS Gen 1 and Gen 2, etc; 
• Experience building Modern ETL process using Azure Data Factory, Azure SSIS IR, Azure File Sync Agent, Data Lake, Data Warehouse, Synapse, Azure SQL Database, U-SQL, Databricks, Azure Functions, SSIS, and Azure Storage; 
• Must have experience in Python, SQL, PowerShell;
• Experience with big data tools: Hadoop, Spark, Kafka (preferred);
• Fluent in English (other languages are a plus).



We kindly ask you to submit your CV in English.
